message.content:
cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LT, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with temporal logic on data words with registers and proposes an extension that allows for specifying a dependency relation on attributes. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the satisfiability problem of Freeze LTL, a temporal logic on data words. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper deals with data words with registers and proposes a way to store and compare collections of attribute values. 
- cs.LT (Computational Linguistics and Natural Language Processing) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with temporal logic. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also less likely but relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of the satisfiability problem of Freeze LTL with ordered attributes.
